## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Migration to Next.js (Recommendation)**:
> Since the backend is currently set up as a separate Express server, hosting it for free in production has major limitations (e.g., Render free tier has a cold-start delay of up to 50 seconds when inactive). 
> **Do you want us to suggest migrating the Express routes into Next.js App Router API routes (`frontend/src/app/api/`)?**
>
> Here are the Pros and Cons of this choice:
> * **Pros**:
>   - **100% Free & Zero Cold Starts**: Vercel hosts both the frontend and backend under a single deploy. Unlike Render, Vercel's serverless functions spin up almost instantly (millisecond range).
>   - **Automatic Scaling**: Vercel handles thousands of concurrent requests automatically out of the box without manual server configuration.
>   - **Unified Deployment**: Deploying is as simple as pushing to GitHub. Database schema changes (Prisma) run automatically on deploy.
> * **Cons**:
>   - **Refactoring Effort**: We have to convert Express routes, request handlers, and middleware to the Next.js API Route format (`NextRequest`, `NextResponse`).
>   - **Execution Time Limits**: Vercel free tier serverless functions have a maximum execution timeout of 10-15 seconds. Heavy tasks (like compiling massive admin reports or complex bulk data operations) might hit this limit.
>   - **Slight Coupling**: The backend logic becomes tied to the Next.js framework (though routes are still standard HTTP REST endpoints that other clients/mobile apps can call).

---

## Detailed Cons of Free-Tier Hosting Providers

We will include a clear table of **cons and limitations** in the report so the business users understand exactly what they are getting with a $0/month budget:

| Service Type | Provider | Free Tier Limit / Con | Impact on Business / User Experience |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Frontend** | Vercel | **100 GB Bandwidth/month**; Commercial usage terms. | If the site becomes popular (e.g., thousands of visitors loading heavy images/videos daily), bandwidth will run out, requiring a paid upgrade ($20/month). |
| **Backend API** | Render / Koyeb | **Web service inactivity sleep** (Render spins down after 15 min of no traffic). | The first customer visiting the site after a quiet period will experience a **30-50 second delay** for the server to wake up (causing high cart abandonment). |
| **Database** | Neon / Supabase | **Auto-suspend database after 24h of inactivity**; **500MB storage limit**. | The database takes 5-10 seconds to wake up on the first request of the day. 500MB storage is plenty for products/orders initially, but will fill up in 6-12 months if user data or audit logs grow. |
| **Media Hosting** | Cloudinary | **25 Credits/month** (~25GB storage or 25k operations). | Uploading high-res product photos without optimization will exhaust free limits quickly. |
| **Payment Gateway** | Razorpay | **No monthly fee, but 2% fee per transaction.** | There is no upfront con, but as volume grows, a flat transaction fee eats into profit margins. |

## Reference Website Analysis Findings

We inspected the three reference links you provided, and here are the core design, layout, and field takeaways we will integrate into the report:

1. **myharvestfarms.com (Freshness & Local Focus)**
   - *Design/Layout*: Fresh green/blue color scheme, announcement banners for promo codes. Custom circular icons for quick category navigation.
   - *Product Fields*: English + Tamil bilingual titles (great for local markets), weight variant selector (250g, 500g, 1kg), price, quantity adjusters, and green "Add to Cart" button.
   - *Key UX Field*: **Delivery Pincode Validator** modal must be entered before adding to cart to verify delivery areas.
   - *Checkout*: Standard Shopify fields (Contact Email, Shipping Name, Address, City, State, Pin Code, Phone) and Razorpay integration.

2. **twobrothersindiashop.com (Premium & Artisanal)**
   - *Design/Layout*: Earthy tones (yellow, cream, brown), rich storytelling sections, sticky Add to Cart buttons.
   - *Product Fields*: Title, subtitle, price, membership pricing teaser, ratings/reviews stars, product features, detailed FAQS, and collapse accordions (Description, Ingredients, Benefits, Storage).
   - *Checkout*: Optimized using **Shopflo Fast-Checkout** (OTP-based mobile login that automatically populates saved address and payment options).

3. **ueirorganic.com (Commercial & Modern Features)**
   - *Design/Layout*: Vibrant green, hero banners, and a sliding subcategory navigation menu above the grid.
   - *Interactive Grid*: **Unique grid layout toggles** (allows users to view in 2, 3, 4, or 5 columns on desktop).
   - *Product Fields*: Stock status (e.g. "In stock"), saving percentage badge, ratings, short summary, and "Buy It Now" button.
   - *Checkout*: Fast-checkout via **Gokwik** with OTP login and integrated coupon-drawer overlays.

